{
  "_meta": {
    "game": "Mario Kart — Super Mario Kart SNES inspired",
    "genre": "kart_racer",
    "source": "SNES Mario Kart mechanics + community analysis",
    "notes": [
      "Mode 7-style pseudo-3D perspective rendering via raycasting scanlines",
      "Physics at 60fps",
      "Speed in pixels/second",
      "Angle in radians"
    ]
  },

  "global": {
    "screen_w": 800,
    "screen_h": 600,
    "horizon_y": 300,
    "fps": 60,
    "max_laps": 3,
    "num_ai_karts": 4,
    "gravity": 0.0,
    "countdown_seconds": 3,
    "music_bpm": 140,
    "notes": [
      "horizon_y splits the screen: above is sky, below is road (Mode 7 scanlines)",
      "The road is rendered per-scanline: each row projects a world-plane y from the camera",
      "Karts and items are billboarded sprites — scaled by (focal_length / distance_z)",
      "Camera: position = kart.x, kart.y; angle = kart.angle; pitched slightly down",
      "focal_length = 200, camera_height = 64, camera_pitch = 0.55 (rads looking down)",
      "Track is a closed polyline of world-space waypoints; road half-width = 180 units",
      "World units: 1 unit ≈ 1 screen pixel at distance 200"
    ]
  },

  "mode7_renderer": {
    "focal_length": 200,
    "camera_height": 64,
    "camera_pitch": 0.55,
    "horizon_y": 300,
    "road_half_width": 180,
    "road_color": [80, 80, 80],
    "grass_color": [34, 139, 34],
    "rumble_color": [200, 40, 40],
    "rumble_width": 24,
    "sky_top_color": [100, 160, 230],
    "sky_bottom_color": [180, 210, 255],
    "fog_start": 600,
    "fog_end": 1200,
    "fog_color": [180, 210, 255],
    "scanline_step": 2,
    "sprite_scale_base": 128,
    "algorithm": [
      "For each screen row y from horizon_y+1 to screen_h:",
      "  row_dist = camera_height * focal_length / (y - horizon_y)",
      "  cos_a = cos(camera_angle), sin_a = sin(camera_angle)",
      "  world_x = camera_x + row_dist * cos_a",
      "  world_y = camera_y + row_dist * sin_a",
      "  step_x = (2 * row_dist) / screen_w * (-sin_a)",
      "  step_y = (2 * row_dist) / screen_w * cos_a",
      "  world_x -= step_x * (screen_w/2); world_y -= step_y * (screen_h/2)",
      "  For each col x: sample road texture at (world_x, world_y), draw pixel, advance step",
      "Sprites: compute screen_x from angle diff, screen_y from horizon to road, scale=focal/dist"
    ]
  },

